---
description: Enforce code quality and maintainability
alwaysApply: true
---

- Prefer simple, readable, modular solutions
- Follow existing patterns unless there is a clear reason to improve them
- Avoid unnecessary complexity
- Keep functions focused
- Keep naming explicit
- Add comments only where they improve clarity
- When touching code, leave it slightly cleaner than you found it
- If tests exist, respect their patterns
- If a risky change is made, document it in the brain files
